    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Refers to the style of art and architecture that coincided with the reign of Mehmed III, from 1595 to 1603. His tomb was designed by Ottoman architect and court artist Ahmed Dalgiç.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000046892/Grove Art Online (2003-2008)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Verwijst naar de stijl van kunst en architectuur die samenviel met de heerschappij van Mehmed III, van 1574 tot 1595. Zijn graftombe werd ontworpen door de Osmaanse architect en hofkunstenaar Ahmed Dalgiç.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052378/Winkler Prins Encyclopedie (1990)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>用來表示西元 1574 年至 1595 年間，與麥哈默德三世統治時期有關的藝術與建築風格。麥哈默德三世的陵墓是由鄂圖曼的建築師兼宮廷藝術家阿赫美德‧達爾吉克（Ahmed Dalgiç）所設計而成。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
